definition.value: A diazaalkane consisting of octane having the two aza groups at the 3- and 6-positions.
An arsenic oxoacid comprising one oxo group and three hydroxy groups attached to a central arsenic atom.
A galactosamine phosphate that is D-galactosamine substituted at position 1 by a monophosphate group.
A glucan that consists of a backbone of alpha-(1->4)-linked glucose residues, most of which are substituted with (1->6)-linked xylose side-chains.
